manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ACDelco Absorbed Glass Mat (AGM) Battery The ACDelco AGM range represents the very best in advanced battery technology for the most highly developed luxury cars and most advanced fuel-saving technology, including Stop/Start and regenerative braking. AGM Plate separators reduce internal resistance, providing significant improvement in all performance criteria, including increased cycling ability, faster recharge acceptance and improved cranking power in Partial-State-Of-Charge (PSOC). The AGM Range is ideal for highly-advanced stop-start vehicles, high-end luxury vehicles that have higher electrical accessory loads or performance vehicles that require a higher CCA starting battery with improved cyclic ability. Battery Benefits ACDelco Full Frame positive & negative charges 100% Maintenance-Free Spill & leak-resistance Highest corrosion-resistance Highest Cold Cranking Amps (CCA) for Stop/Start Applications Pressurised internally for vibration resistance Mandatory replacement for cars fitted with AGM batteries as original fit Ability to be retro fitted as a "higher performance" option in high load applications

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this battery for my 2016 BMW M-Spec 328i. Exact fit to replace the original BMW-labled battery that came with the car. I kept the memory in my car before i disconnect the old battery, put this ACDelco in, programed it to my car so that the car can communicate with it properly and all is fine.My engine stop and go system works fine and everything else works great, put my battery analyzer on and it is reading great, when engine is off and when engine is on, also when load is applied, such as headlights, hazard lights, AC, radio etc.great product. If I get a life span of three and a half years or even three years, that would be great, would definitely purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Used to replace a 3 year old interstate battery that was starting to drain. So far cat is starting much easier and I am able to sit with the engine off and electric on for much longer without fearing not being able to start the engine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars The Battery Does Not Fit as Described, It Cannot be Returned as Gurantee on the Page
reviews.reviewText: The description on the Amazon page of this ACDelco Gold 49AGMHR shows it fits the Kia Sedona 2016. However, it doesn't fit. It's longer than the battery tray and, therefore, you cannot secure it down. The positive terminal doesn't allow room to connect. The shipping also slightly cracked the edge of the battery. The BIGGEST problem is when I request a return, it says this item cannot be returned, even though it says on this page it can be returned. Money and time wasted. Felt robbed!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Best price I found for this battery.
reviews.reviewText: Diagnosed my battery to be failing and the need to replace was dire. Did some searching and although it's an expensive battery (I know lithium batteries are ridiculous), this was the most reasonable price I found. Sorta straight forward installation in a 2007 Mercedes S550, albeit a bit of work crawling into the trunk to R&R.Note: If things like comfort setting aren't working properly or your radio and climate control start shutting down sooner than expected, these are all signs of a failing battery.Note 2: Specifically on the 2007 S550, there are two batteries in the car. Check with someone/place that knows for sure for your vehicle.
